name: ACCC sues Coles Woolworths
summary: The Australian Competition and Consumer Commission (ACCC) has initiated lawsuits against supermarket giants Woolworths and Coles for allegedly misleading consumers about discounts on over 500 products. The retailers are accused of using "illusory" discounts, where the "was" price is artificially inflated to make the discounted price appear more substantial. The ACCC claims that these practices have contributed to rising inflation, leading Prime Minister Anthony Albanese to express concern. The lawsuit alleges that the retailers have engaged in "very serious" conduct and aims to address consumer concerns about deceptive pricing practices in the grocery industry.

This has raised concerns about the team's ability to compete for the Premier League title, as they have lost a third of their league games without him. Many believe that Rodri's absence will make manager Pep Guardiola's job much harder. The injury has also been described as a "disaster" for City and a significant blow for the Spanish national team. While some have questioned whether Rodri is the best in the world, there is no doubt that his presence has been crucial to City's recent success.
